    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-19T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-19T21:00:00-05:00" n="776"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.6712A/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-19T21:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1928—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. Department’s 37, April 13, 6 p.m. The Department today handed Turkish
                    Ambassador drafts of proposed treaties of arbitration and of conciliation. The
                    texts of the proposed treaties will be forwarded in the next pouch.<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d776fn11">Draft treaties not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
